    "2026-07-02 H6a-smoke — Manual real-host smoke prep + two defects it surfaced. (1) tests/fixtures/h7a/acceptance.loom used `#` comments, but loom's comment syntax is `//`/`///` (lexer.ts); every `#` line lexed as source and the prose \"schema lowering/validation\" on line 12 tripped loom/parse/schema-case-mismatch@12:58. The H7a in-process gate models the pipeline and never lexes/parses the fixture text, so the invalid fixture shipped green. Fixed `#`→`//` (parses to 0 diagnostics; loom-smoke.loom parses clean, unchanged). Also re-pinned the fixture binder model from the unresolvable anthropic:claude-sonnet (colon separator loom's matcher does not split on; no anthropic model has id claude-sonnet) to anthropic/claude-opus-4-8. (2) The emitted load diagnostic crashed Pi's TUI (\"Rendered line 33 exceeds terminal width (122 > 80)\"): src/extension/system-note-renderer.ts textComponent.render(width) ignored width and returned lines verbatim, so any diagnostic wider than the terminal crashes the host at load. The double-backed tests never invoke render(width) against the TUI width contract, so it shipped. Fixed: render(width) now wraps each line ANSI-aware via pi-tui wrapTextWithAnsi (blank line preserved; non-positive width falls back to raw). Added wrapTextWithAnsi as a peer-named-import to SDK_SURFACE_INVENTORY (inventory-closure audit stays green). Regression tests added to tests/system-note-channel.test.ts (long diagnostic wraps so no rendered line exceeds width; blank-line + non-positive-width fallback). Also changed tests/live/harness.ts requireLiveProvider() to prefer claude-opus-4-8 (then any opus) over the cheap/haiku list. npm test 1468 green; typecheck + lint + inventory-closure-audit clean. Spec/test gap recorded: no render-width contract exists for the loom-system-note renderer.",
